cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.ST

The paper deals with the problem of forecasting conditional probabilities, which is a common topic in machine learning and statistics. The focus on constructing a single predictor that performs as well as the best predictor in a large, uncountable set of predictors suggests that the paper belongs to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Bayesian predictors and the consideration of regret also suggest that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The general probabilistic setting and the consideration of sets of predictors also suggest that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and statistics (cs.ST).
